{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we select the best instruction to serve as the input for the task.• Demonstration examples are selected from a candidate set {s i }.",
    "Unlike instruction generation, example selection depends on the input x.",
    "If an example is more similar to the input, it provides more relevant information to the LLM.",
    "Specifically, we learn an input encoder E X (⋅) and an example encoder E S (⋅), and calculate the similarity between E X (x) and E S (s i) for all candidate examples using L2 distance [2,22,24].",
    "For instance, if x and s i are both SQLs, they may share similar operators such as COUNT(⋅) or JOIN."
  ]
}